  "instructions": [
    "Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, and salt in a bowl.",
    "Stir in olive oil and warm water until a smooth dough forms.",
    "Cover the dough and let it ferment at room temperature for 24 hours.",
    "Roll out the dough thinly, cut into circles, and wrap each around a cannoli form, sealing the edges with water.",
    "Bake the shells at 375°F for 18 minutes, then cool on a rack.",
    "Mix ricotta, almond milk, vanilla, and half the cherries until creamy.",
    "Fill each shell with the ricotta mixture using a pastry bag or spoon.",
    "Top filled cannoli with remaining cherries and a sprinkle of chocolate chips, dust with powdered sugar before serving."
